 First, let's have a look at this expression:
  \begin{align}
\frac{x^2+2-\sqrt{x^4+4}}{x} = {} &x + \frac{2}{x} -\sqrt{x^2+\frac{4}{x^2}}\\
\end{align}
  Now let us complete the square:
  \begin{align}
 x + \frac{2}{x} -\sqrt{x^2+\frac{4}{x^2}} = {} &x+1 + \frac{2}{x} -\sqrt{\left(x+\frac{2}{x}\right)^2 -4}\\
  \end{align}
 <end think> 
<answer>$\sqrt{3}$</answer>

